                <componentInstanceProperties>
                    <name>richTextValue</name>
                    <value>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Action Definition: JSON Schema Guidance&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Configure how this Action interacts with the framework using JSON Schema.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1. LLM Input Parameter Schema (JSON Schema)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Purpose:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Defines arguments required &lt;em&gt;from the LLM&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; when it invokes this Action. Acts as the input contract for the LLM.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Format:&lt;/strong&gt; Standard JSON Schema (similar to OpenAI functions). Must be {&quot;type&quot;: &quot;object&quot;, ...}.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Structure:&lt;/strong&gt; Define properties (arguments) with their type (string, number, boolean, etc.) and description. Use required: [...] list for mandatory arguments.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; (For an action needing recordId and optional comment)&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;object&quot;, &quot;properties&quot;: {&quot;recordId&quot;: {&quot;type&quot;: &quot;string&quot;, &quot;description&quot;: &quot;The Salesforce ID of the target record&quot;}, &quot;comment&quot;: {&quot;type&quot;: &quot;string&quot;, &quot;description&quot;: &quot;Optional comment&quot;}}, &quot;required&quot;: [&quot;recordId&quot;]}&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;No Params?:&lt;/strong&gt; Use {&quot;type&quot;: &quot;object&quot;, &quot;properties&quot;: {}}.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2. Binding Config Schema (JSON Schema - Optional)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Purpose:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Defines the structure for backend configuration&lt;/strong&gt; needed when &lt;em&gt;binding&lt;/em&gt; this Action to an Agent (ActionConfiguration on the Binding record).&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Format:&lt;/strong&gt; Standard JSON Schema, like above.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Use Case:&lt;/strong&gt; Needed only if the Action&apos;s &lt;em&gt;backend logic&lt;/em&gt; (Apex/Flow) requires specific settings that might vary per Agent (e.g., target object, default values).&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; (If backend needs a target Record Type API name)&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;{&quot;type&quot;: &quot;object&quot;, &quot;properties&quot;: {&quot;targetRecordTypeApiName&quot;: {&quot;type&quot;: &quot;string&quot;, &quot;description&quot;: &quot;API Name of the Record Type to use&quot;}}, &quot;required&quot;: [&quot;targetRecordTypeApiName&quot;]}&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Leave Blank:&lt;/strong&gt; If the Action logic doesn&apos;t need unique settings per agent binding.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</value>
                </componentInstanceProperties>
